cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a security vulnerability in the ARM TrustZone technology and proposes an attack that exploits it. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the verification process of the system and how it affects the security of the trusted environment. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and implementation of trusted execution environments in processors. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the architecture of the ARM TrustZone technology and how it can be exploited. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages, but it does discuss the implementation of software in the trusted environment.
